parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver's seat recliner mechanism can cause the seat to unexpectedly recline or collapse, leading to loss of control of the vehicle, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The seat reclines or collapses unexpectedly
the seat does not stay in the upright position
the seat moves back while driving
the seatback collapses when pressure is applied
the seat reclines to the fully reclined position upon impact.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure and stalling can cause the vehicle to become inoperable, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine shuts down while driving
engine failure
vehicle stalling
loss of power
engine surging
RPM surging.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Motor mount failure can cause the engine to move excessively, leading to premature wear on other components, and potentially causing the engine to fail or stall.
symptoms: Loose motor mount
motor mount failure
engine shaking
vibration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Timing chain failure can cause the engine to fail, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Timing chain failure
engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cooling system issues can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine failure or damage.
symptoms: Temperature gauge goes to the red
overheating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: PCV hose failure can cause the engine to seize, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: PCV hose freezing
oil forced out of the crankcase
engine seizure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to a lack of proper restraint in the event of an accident, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The seat belt retractor fails to move out of the way when the door is opened
the seat belt retracts and tightens severely
the seat belt opens up during sudden stops
the seat belt track is inoperative
the seat belt is stuck in the track
the passive restraint is stuck forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inoperability of the seat belt can cause the driver or passenger to be unrestrained in the event of an accident, leading to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The seat belt does not move when the door is opened
the seat belt is stuck in the track
the passive restraint is stuck forward
the seat belt does not retract
the seat belt does not tighten properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the seat can cause the driver or passenger to be unrestrained or improperly restrained in the event of an accident, leading to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The driver's seat reclines automatically under acceleration
the seat belt track is inoperative
the seat belt does not hold the driver in place during an accident
the front seats are forced rearward and land on the back seats during an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents, injuries, or even fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the vehicle swerves or pulls to one side while braking
the brakes feel spongy or soft
the brakes make a grinding noise
the vehicle rolls while stopping with brakes applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of rotors and failure of brake lining can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents, injuries, or even fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes make a grinding noise
the rotors are corroded
the brake lining peels off
the vehicle takes longer to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or even fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS system locks up
the vehicle swerves or pulls to one side while braking
the brakes make a grinding noise.
